Unknown gunmen have attacked Kidandan and Kadai villages leaving twelve (12)) people dead and seven others seriously injured. The attackers invaded the area in their numbers besieged on Friday afternoon and left three dead and four others wounded. The gunmen who continued their heinous act on Saturday killed nine other persons at Kadai village and left four others in critical condition. The Kaduna State Police Command Spokesman Muhammad Jalige confirmed the report when DAILY POST contacted him. Also confirming the attack, the District Head of Fatika and Kaigaman Zazzau, Alhaji Nuhu Lawal Umar, appealed to the government to deploy additional security personnel to safeguard the lives and property of people in the area.